You will be a technically intense workload expert within the Microsoft enterprise sales organization working with our most important customers. You play a key role in the total sales cycle by helping them with their end-to-end business transformation needs through envisioning, designing and demonstrating solutions mapped to business value within the area of your workload expertise. Executing with excellence you will collaborate across the sales opportunity journey with the Business Applications sales team, Microsoft partners and ISVs, other Technical Specialists and our Customer Success team. 
Responsibilities 
The Business Applications Technical Specialist  is a key member of the Business Applications sales pursuit team and is a strategic thinker, proactive problem solver, sales & technical roadblock resolver displaying a growth mindset with deep functional and technical knowledge in the workload. 
The following are the role responsibilities for the Microsoft Business Applications Technical Specialist: 
You will partner with a Business Applications Sales Executive in sales pursuit, in envisioning solution using ISV components, by assembling and collaborating with a technical pursuit team that includes partner and ISV resources .
 You will drive the advancement of the Power Platform and the of the overall Biz Apps Cloud / Power Platform portfolio, also encompassing the Dynamics 365 (CRM/ERP) business solutions areas such as: Sales, Marketing, Customer Service, Field Service, Supply Chain, Manufacturing, Retail/Commerce and or/ Finance. 
You will partner with a Bus Apps sales executive, your strategic global account teams and customer success manager to build the business case for the Power Platform / Dynamics 365 (CRM/ERP) Business Solution Portfolio 
You will be the subject matter expert for your Time Zone sales team for Dynamics 365, Power Platform development ecosystem; and will lead competitive strategy for the Power Platform within your account teams. 
You will work with your account teams to obtain a strong understanding of each accountâ€™s governance and decision processes and the customerâ€™s business & technology priorities. 
